# Server Admin Popup Config - Overview

## Purpose
Allow server admins to configure the server welcome popup UI elements displayed to users.

## Requirements
- Admin-only access (check permissions)
- Configure 7 fields:
  - Server name
  - Server icon URL
  - Server banner URL
  - Server time format (12h/24h)
  - Message of the Day (MOTD)
  - Customized welcome message
  - Events section (empty placeholder for future)
- Save changes to database
- Load existing config on form open
- Real-time validation (URL format, text limits)
- Preview changes (optional enhancement)

## User Flow
1. Admin opens server settings → navigates to "Popup Config" tab
2. Form loads with current server config
3. Admin edits fields → clicks Save
4. Changes persist to database
5. Users see updated popup on next login

## Scope
- Backend: API endpoints for GET/PUT config
- Frontend: Admin form UI component
- Database: Extend server table or create config table
- Permissions: Verify MANAGE_SERVER permission

## Future Extensions
- Events section will support announcements, polls, scheduled messages
- Preview mode to see popup as users would
- Template system for welcome messages
